      "message": "Hi @chaul@amperecomputing.com. I made a pldmtool functionality based off your PLDM_File_Transfer support.\n\n```\n pldmtool file ReadFile -h\nRead data from a PLDM File Descriptor (-p \u003cpath\u003e | -i \u003cindex from ListFiles\u003e)\nUsage: pldmtool file ReadFile [OPTIONS]\n\nOptions:\n  -h,--help                   Print this help message and exit\n  -p,--object-path TEXT       D-Bus object path of the PLDM File\n  -i,--index INT              Index from \u0027pldmtool file ListFiles\u0027 (use instead of -p)\n  -o,--offset UINT            Byte offset to start reading from (default: 0)\n  -l,--length UINT            Number of bytes to read, 0 means whole file (default: 0)\n  -f,--output-file TEXT       Write raw bytes to this path instead of hex-dumping to stdout\n  -x,--exclusive              Request exclusive access to the file\n\n```\n\nAppreciate your review. I want your opinion on whether the pldmtool options need any addition/removal.",
